00:00:02,060 --> 00:00:06,019
A painter, Johan Borg,
disappeared some years ago

2
00:00:06,860 --> 00:00:10,978
from the small frisian island
of Baltrum.

3
00:00:12,500 --> 00:00:16,459
His wife Alma since gave me Johan's diary,
found among his left papers.

4
00:00:17,300 --> 00:00:21,259
This diary and her stories

5
00:00:22,180 --> 00:00:25,536
are the basis of the film.

6
00:00:30,460 --> 00:00:31,859
THE HOUR OF THE WOLF

7
00:01:26,180 --> 00:01:28,375
Silence! Take!

8
00:01:33,500 --> 00:01:34,250
Camera !

9
00:02:15,340 --> 00:02:16,216
No...

10
00:02:17,900 --> 00:02:19,618
I can't tell you this.

11
00:02:24,460 --> 00:02:26,212
You were given the diary..

12
00:02:30,300 --> 00:02:32,860
You wonder why I stay on here ?

13
00:02:34,740 --> 00:02:37,334
We lived here for 7 years,
together.

14
00:02:40,140 --> 00:02:43,257
This winter, I can go
to the mainland

15
00:02:43,460 --> 00:02:45,496
to work in the shop,
like I did before,

16
00:02:45,700 --> 00:02:47,656
when we were short of money.

17
00:02:53,820 --> 00:02:56,015
The baby will be born in a month.

18
00:02:57,780 --> 00:03:01,136
I went to see the doctor before
going out here the last time.

19
00:03:05,580 --> 00:03:07,377
It was on a friday I remember.

20
00:03:08,780 --> 00:03:12,056
Quite late, at 10 I believe.

21
00:03:14,140 --> 00:03:16,210
But it was still light outside.

22
00:03:20,820 --> 00:03:23,857
I plan on staying here
until August.

23
00:03:26,220 --> 00:03:28,097
We wanted to be completely alone.

24
00:03:30,540 --> 00:03:32,371
He did not want to see anyone here.

25
00:03:32,900 --> 00:03:34,094
He was scared...

26
00:03:45,180 --> 00:03:47,899
He liked that I was quiet.

27
00:03:49,940 --> 00:03:51,373
He liked...

28
00:03:59,380 --> 00:04:02,178
We arrived here
at 3 in the morning.

29
00:04:02,820 --> 00:04:05,653
On the beach,
there was a shed.

30
00:04:08,940 --> 00:04:11,010
We were happy to find the

31
00:04:11,220 --> 00:04:13,450
apple tree in bloom.

32
00:04:14,660 --> 00:04:16,696
Later, we found footprints

33
00:04:17,540 --> 00:04:19,258
outside the kitchen window

34
00:04:19,460 --> 00:04:21,371
Johan didn't like that,

35
00:04:22,100 --> 00:04:24,216
but we didn't think more about
it until...

36
00:04:31,260 --> 00:04:32,534
We were happy.

37
00:04:34,540 --> 00:04:36,770
Happy to be at home again.

38
00:04:39,940 --> 00:04:41,692
Johan was a bit uneasy

39
00:04:42,380 --> 00:04:44,575
because his work was not going well.

40
00:04:44,860 --> 00:04:46,930
It had been like that for a while.

41
00:04:50,100 --> 00:04:52,136
He slept poorly.

42
00:04:53,660 --> 00:04:54,615
He was afraid.

43
00:04:55,460 --> 00:04:57,371
Scared of the dark in a way.

44
00:05:00,820 --> 00:05:03,175
It had become harder in the
last years.

45
00:08:10,340 --> 00:08:11,090
I have an idea !

46
00:08:12,260 --> 00:08:13,659
I want to draw you.

47
00:08:16,700 --> 00:08:18,053
Go sit over there.

48
00:08:19,460 --> 00:08:21,530
Move over !

49
00:08:23,460 --> 00:08:24,939
Back up a bit.

50
00:08:27,820 --> 00:08:29,014
Are you cold ?

51
00:08:29,660 --> 00:08:33,448
Sit like you use to.

52
00:08:34,660 --> 00:08:37,049
Pull down your robe a bit.
Disclose your shoulders.

53
00:08:39,740 --> 00:08:43,574
Release your hair,
so I can see your neck.

54
00:08:45,740 --> 00:08:48,413
That's it. Where are my glasses ?

55
00:08:53,820 --> 00:08:55,378
Good. Sit like that.

56
00:09:02,820 --> 00:09:06,608
Like I patiently draw you
day after day.

57
00:10:40,740 --> 00:10:41,650
Look.

58
00:10:44,540 --> 00:10:47,259
I never showed this to anyone.

59
00:10:50,060 --> 00:10:51,891
This is the most common.

60
00:10:52,100 --> 00:10:53,818
Practically without defense.

61
00:10:55,020 --> 00:10:56,692
I think he is homosexual.

62
00:10:59,900 --> 00:11:01,379
The old lady

63
00:11:01,900 --> 00:11:04,050
threatening to remove her hat.

64
00:11:04,420 --> 00:11:05,409
Do you know hat will happen
if she does ?

65
00:11:06,940 --> 00:11:08,976
Her face will follow with it !

66
00:11:15,220 --> 00:11:16,812
Here, this is the worst of them.

67
00:11:17,700 --> 00:11:19,691
I call him the Birdman.

68
00:11:20,580 --> 00:11:23,333
I don't know if it is a real beak
or just a mask.

69
00:11:25,820 --> 00:11:27,651
He is very fast.

70
00:11:29,220 --> 00:11:31,859
As if he were related to Papageno
in The Magic Flute.

71
00:11:35,100 --> 00:11:38,979
The others, the carnivores,
the insects...

72
00:11:40,860 --> 00:11:42,691
especially the spidermen.

73
00:11:45,100 --> 00:11:47,614
And the school teacher,
with his stick...

74
00:11:51,020 --> 00:11:52,373
And then these...

75
00:11:53,060 --> 00:11:56,257
tattling metal-hard women ...

76
00:11:59,980 --> 00:12:01,618
I have to stay awake awhile.

77
00:12:13,700 --> 00:12:15,656
In an hour it will be day...

78
00:12:18,700 --> 00:12:19,894
then I can sleep.

79
00:12:47,620 --> 00:12:50,054
A minute
is really a long timespan.

80
00:12:51,580 --> 00:12:52,899
It starts...

81
00:13:01,540 --> 00:13:02,609
10 seconds.

82
00:13:15,780 --> 00:13:17,293
Oh, these seconds !

83
00:13:20,220 --> 00:13:21,972
See how long they last !

84
00:13:29,260 --> 00:13:31,012
Still not a minute.

85
00:13:49,580 --> 00:13:50,854
There it is !

86
00:13:52,340 --> 00:13:53,739
Now it is gone.

87
00:14:02,220 --> 00:14:03,699
Say something.

88
00:14:04,940 --> 00:14:06,293
Talk to me, Alma.

89
00:14:13,900 --> 00:14:16,368
I've been thinking about something
for a while...

90
00:14:17,980 --> 00:14:19,254
Are you listening ?

91
00:14:24,020 --> 00:14:27,137
Our life together for seven years...

92
00:14:28,220 --> 00:14:30,336
No, that's not what I was going to say.

93
00:14:30,540 --> 00:14:31,734
I know.

94
00:14:33,220 --> 00:14:35,654
Isn't it so that people living together
for a long time

95
00:14:35,860 --> 00:14:39,296
start to resemble one another ?

96
00:14:40,940 --> 00:14:43,773
The develop so many things in
common.

97
00:14:44,300 --> 00:14:46,336
Not just their thoughts...

98
00:14:46,540 --> 00:14:49,008
Their faces
get a similar expression.

99
00:14:51,140 --> 00:14:52,858
Why do you think that happens ?

100
00:14:58,020 --> 00:15:01,774
I wish for us to become so old
together

101
00:15:02,860 --> 00:15:04,737
that we start thinking eachother's thoughts.

102
00:15:06,980 --> 00:15:10,097
And develop similar, dried-up
wrinkled faces.

103
00:15:11,140 --> 00:15:12,732
What do you think about that ?

104
00:15:18,820 --> 00:15:20,048
Are you sleeping ?

105
00:15:23,860 --> 00:15:25,418
Let's go, Johan.

106
00:15:26,180 --> 00:15:28,057
Let's go to bed.

107
00:16:54,260 --> 00:16:58,458
Don't look so alarmed.
I'm not dangerous.

108
00:16:59,940 --> 00:17:01,259
Give me your hand.

109
00:17:03,700 --> 00:17:05,258
Do you feel my hand now ?

110
00:17:06,580 --> 00:17:10,209
The fingers, the veins under
the skin ?

111
00:17:11,380 --> 00:17:14,258
At my age, the hands are a bit cold.

112
00:17:15,140 --> 00:17:17,700
Anyway, I'm 216 years old.

113
00:17:22,060 --> 00:17:23,493
No, I wanted to say 76 !

114
00:17:26,740 --> 00:17:29,777
I should be going.

115
00:17:31,860 --> 00:17:34,090
Wait !
What was I going to say ?

116
00:17:34,700 --> 00:17:36,850
I remember.

117
00:17:37,660 --> 00:17:40,936
In his black bag,

118
00:17:41,540 --> 00:17:42,893
under the bed
Is the book with drwaings....

119
00:17:54,220 --> 00:17:55,892
One more thing.

120
00:17:56,100 --> 00:17:59,012
In the same bag is his diary.

121
00:17:59,620 --> 00:18:00,769
Read it !

122
00:19:42,540 --> 00:19:45,816
Wednesday, 22 of July :
I've been sick.

123
00:19:46,820 --> 00:19:49,937
Nothing serious,
but quite unpleasant.

124
00:20:25,500 --> 00:20:27,775
Sorry for disturbing you.
I have for several days,

125
00:20:27,980 --> 00:20:30,369
been looking for a way to
approach you .

126
00:20:30,820 --> 00:20:33,050
I've chosen to go straight at you.

127
00:20:33,260 --> 00:20:35,728
I'm baron von Merkens.

128
00:20:37,060 --> 00:20:39,813
As you may know,
I own this island.

129
00:20:40,020 --> 00:20:42,011
I live in the old castle on the northern
part.

130
00:20:43,140 --> 00:20:46,928
Would you and your wife like to have
dinner with us ?

131
00:20:47,580 --> 00:20:48,774
That's very kind.

132
00:20:48,980 --> 00:20:52,416
